{:proof/problem-id "apm-t94J08", :proof/classification :partial, :proof/output "\n\n---\n\nTARGET SANITY CHECK — mentions-problem-objects? ✅ (explicitly talks about the antipodal map on \\(S^n\\), vector fields \\(v,-v\\), and local indices at the isolated zero \\(p\\)) · avoids-assuming-conclusion? ✅ (the formal targets only assume orientation/parity facts and ask for the degree/local-index values) · meaningful-without-prose? ✅ (each EDN statement, by itself, captures the exact claims of parts (a) and (b)) · notes: helper lemma isolates how negating a vector field affects its local index, while the main claim computes the antipodal degree via orientation parity.\n\n```\nPROOF-PLAN.EDN\n{:goal \"Relate orientation parity to degrees and local indices for the antipodal map and vector fields.\" \n :terms [{:name \"degree parity\"\n          :meaning \"For maps S^n → S^n, the degree detects whether the map preserves or reverses orientation; antipodal map has degree (-1)^{n+1}.\"\n          :needed-because \"Once the degree is known, the local index statements follow from how vector fields transform under orientation reversal.\"}\n         {:name \"local index\"\n          :meaning \"Degree of the normalized vector field map S^{n-1} → S^{n-1} surrounding an isolated zero.\"\n          :needed-because \"This definition lets us compare the indices of v and -v by understanding the effect of negating the vector field on that sphere map.\"}\n         {:name \"orientation reversal\"\n          :meaning \"The antipodal map acts by −Id on tangent spaces, reversing orientation iff n is even.\"\n          :needed-because \"Determining whether −Id preserves orientation is the key step in computing both the map degree and the sign change of the local index.\"}]\n :strategy [{:id :s1\n             :formal-dependency \"degree_of_linear_orientation_map\"\n             :informal-dependency \"Stage 1 part (a) uses the determinant of −Id\"\n             :why-this-now \"The degree equals the determinant sign of the linear approximation, which for −Id is (−1)^{n+1}.\"\n             :lean-target \"degree_antipodal_and_index_negation\"\n             :mathlib-status \"Mathlib has linear-algebra facts about determinants, but sphere-degree and local-index APIs are still sparse.\"}]\n :stage-status {:stage1 :done :stage2 :done :stage3 :in-progress :stage4 :pending}}\n```\n\n```\nFORMAL-ALIGNMENT.EDN\n{:main-claim {:informal-claim \"The antipodal map on S^n has degree (−1)^{n+1}.\"\n             :formal-name \"degree_antipodal\"\n             :formal-target \"For each integer n≥0, the continuous map a_n : S^n → S^n, x ↦ −x, has deg(a_n) = (−1)^{n+1}.\"\n             :sanity-check {:mentions-problem-objects? true\n                            :avoids-assuming-conclusion? true\n                            :meaningful-without-prose? true\n                            :notes \"This is exactly part (a).\"}}\n :alignments [{:formal-name \"degree_antipodal\"\n              :formal-statement \"∀ n, deg(x ↦ −x on S^n) = (−1)^{n+1}.\"\n              :informal-clause \"Stage 1 statement in part (a)\"\n              :role :main-theorem}\n             {:formal-name \"local_index_negated_field\"\n              :formal-statement \"If v has isolated zero at p with local index d, then −v has local index (−1)^n·d.\"\n              :informal-clause \"Stage 1 statement in part (b)\"\n              :role :helper-lemma}]}\n```\n\n---\n\n**Completed write-up.** The antipodal map \\(x\\mapsto -x\\) acts as \\(-\\mathrm{Id}\\) on each tangent space of \\(S^n\\), so its degree is \\((\\det(-\\mathrm{Id}_{\\mathbb R^{n+1}})) = (-1)^{n+1}\\). For a vector field \\(v\\) with isolated zero at \\(p\\), the local index is the degree of the normalized map on a small linking sphere. Negating \\(v\\) composes that map with the antipodal map on \\(S^{n-1}\\), so the index picks up the factor \\((-1)^n\\). These arguments (with “Why it’s hard”, “Key insight”, and the full proof) now live in `/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t94J08/apm-v2-t94J08-1775011677105/execute.md`, along with Stage 2’s dependency graph, Stage 3’s status, and the Stage 4 reflection.\n\n**Frame artifacts.**  \n- `proof-plan.edn` specifies the goal, three key terms (degree parity, local index, orientation reversal), one strategy item, and stage-status `{... :stage3 :in-progress :stage4 :pending}`.  \n- `formal-alignment.edn` records the main claim “degree of the antipodal map” and the helper lemma “local index of −v equals (−1)^n times the original.”  \n- `changelog.edn` now has entries for workspace initialization, Stage 1–2 completion, and the Stage 3 attempt.  \n\n**Lean status / blocker.** The Lean file `/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/T94J08/Apm_v2_t94J08_1775011677105/Main.lean` is still a stub because Mathlib presently lacks:\n1. A general definition/API for the degree of smooth self-maps of \\(S^n\\) (beyond low-dimensional special cases).\n2. Any formal definition of the local index of a vector field.\n\nWithout those foundations, the intended theorem cannot even be stated, so `lake build ApmCanaries.Frames.T94J08.Apm_v2_t94J08_1775011677105.Main` still fails—not due to lingering `sorry`s, but because the necessary concepts do not exist yet. The Stage 3 section of `execute.md` documents this precise gap; once Mathlib gains sphere-degree and local-index infrastructure, the formal proof can follow the Stage 1 argument directly.", :proof/extraction {:phases {}, :dependency-graph nil, :arse-questions nil, :classification :partial, :phase-count 0, :dep-graph-count 0, :arse-count 0}, :proof/frame-workspace {:frame/lean-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/T94J08/Apm_v2_t94J08_1775011677105", :frame/id "apm-v2-t94J08-1775011677105", :workspace/owner-repo "futon6", :workspace/generated-at "2026-04-01T02:47:57.128508Z", :frame/shared-extension-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Local", :frame/module-root "ApmCanaries.Frames.T94J08.Apm_v2_t94J08_1775